dh_parameters.name: cryptopals-group-33-small
dh_parameters.description: Parameters for Cryptopals Problem 33 (small example). NOT FOR PRODUCTION USE.
dh_parameters.notes: p=37 (hex: 25), g=5 (hex: 05). Used for learning purposes. Insecure for real applications.

dh_parameters.name: rfc3526-group-14
dh_parameters.description: RFC 3526 Group 14 (2048-bit MODP Group). Recommended for general use.
dh_parameters.notes: This is a widely used and secure group. The 'p' value is the same as the Cryptopals 'bignum' parameter. 'g' is 2. Values are hexadecimal strings for easy parsing.

dh_parameters.name: rfc3526-group-15
dh_parameters.description: RFC 3526 Group 15 (3072-bit MODP Group). Higher security than Group 14.
dh_parameters.notes: A stronger group for increased security requirements.

dh_parameters.name: rfc3526-group-16
dh_parameters.description: RFC 3526 Group 16 (4096-bit MODP Group). Higher security than Group 15.
dh_parameters.notes: A stronger group for increased security requirements.

dh_parameters.name: rfc3526-group-17
dh_parameters.description: RFC 3526 Group 17 (6144-bit MODP Group). Higher security than Group 16.

dh_parameters.name: rfc3526-group-18
dh_parameters.description: RFC 3526 Group 18 (8192-bit MODP Group). Higher security than Group 17.
